The war against drugs wages on in Phoenix with members of SAPS Phoenix Crime Prevention Unit arresting more than 50 individuals for drugs such as cocaine, heroin and mandrax, over the past week.Phoenix SAPS communications officer Captain Louise Naidoo said, “One such case which stands out is where Warrant Officer Chendriah and his members arrested a suspect for being in possession of 1 000 capsules of heroin at Rucklen Place in the notorious Barnyard drug den.” “We are committed to clean the streets of Phoenix and we urge the community to maintain their anonymity and help us to weed out the scourge of drugs in the area. Together we can make a difference,” said Cpt Naidoo. Cpt Naidoo said that investigations are ongoing.